709128f-a.text:
5th Avenue, east side, at E. 69th Street, showing
private dellings at both the N.E. and S.E. corners. These in order are (or were) the Adolph Lewisohn (No.881), the E.H. Harriman (No. 1 E. 69th Street), the Ueden Mills (No.877)
and the Daniel J. Leary (No. 876) homes.
The N.Y. Herald Tribune of Sunday, June 18, 1939 carries a photo and an article reporting the details of the proposed Nreplacement with an apartment house of the iarriman and possibly the Lewisohn homes. Sir John Mactaggart, a Scottish builder purchased the former 5 years ago and is about to procede with plans for this
site.
View 2 shows only the Levisohn and Harriman homes while
No.3 features only the latter.
